Tim Cook is all but assured to be Apple’s boss into 2025, when 1 million shares designed to keep him at the helm finish paying out. Then what?

If he decided he wanted to stay on, Apple’s board would be more than happy to let him — but there are signs that's not likely. Whenever he goes, he'll vacate a critical role overseeing a multitrillion-dollar empire with well over 100,000 employees.

@MarkGurman takes a look at 11 runners and riders for one of the biggest jobs in tech. Tap the link in our bio for more in our free-to-read newsletter, Power On.
